radiographic_examinations.findings: The visualized lung bases are clear without pleural effusions. The liver enhances homogeneously without focal lesions. The gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, adrenal glands, and kidneys are normal. There is prompt excretion of IV contrast into the collecting system bilaterally without hydronephrosis and hydroureter. The stomach, duodenum and loops of small bowel are normal and patent with oral contrast. The appendix is fluid filled, measuring up to 12 mm in maximum diameter. Periappendiceal fat stranding is mild. No free air, fluid or lymphadenopathy in the intra-abdominal cavity or pelvis.
